{
  "stem": "26699.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The first bombing of Bucharest, which took on the fourth of April, 1944, so a couple of weeks after our arrival in Bucharest-- took the lives of about 10,000 people in one hour.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] A hail of bombs was dropped over the civilian part of the town because the tactic of the American and the British Army was to terrorize the Germans, to terrorize the Romanians in order to get them to surrender.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So this was the first blow in the morning, 10 o'clock in the morning of fourth of April.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But in this respect, Jews or non-Jews-- they were equal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I can say also, to the defense of the Romanian population, that after this morning, there were some public aircraft shelters in the basements of high rise buildings, and the Jews were accepted as equals with the Christians in the same shelters, whilst in other places and other countries, Jews would have been left to die in the street.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They gave us the same accommodation as they had for themselves, and this was very much appreciated.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, the bombings carried on day and night, day and night, without any respite for [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] four months, solid four months, from April to August, with victims and so on.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "After two months of not sleeping in the night and not sleeping in the day, and everything being destroyed, and no food, no water, nothing, a lot of people decided to leave Bucharest and to go to the countryside.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we moved to the countryside.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My father's brother had a connection, and they moved to a village about 60 kilometers south of Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I still remember the name, Stanca.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we were safe there.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
